onal keyword arguments passed to Matplotlib's figure() function\n    if a new figure is created.\n\nReturns\n-------\ntuple\n    A tuple containing:\n        - fig: The Matplotlib figure object.\n        - ax: The Matplotlib axes object."]}, {"name": "pyvlasiator.plot.plot.set_args", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "meta", "type": {"name": "Vlsv", "xref": {"fqname": "pyvlasiator.vlsv.Vlsv", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "var", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "axisunit", "type": {"name": "AxisUnit", "xref": {"fqname": "pyvlasiator.plot.plot.AxisUnit", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "dir", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "origin", "type": {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "PlotArgs", "xref": {"fqname": "PlotArgs", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Set plot-related arguments of `var` in `axisunit`.\n\n# Parameters\n\nvar\n\n: Variable name from the VLSV file.\n\naxisunit\n\n: Unit of the axis.\n\ndir\n\n: Normal direction of the 2D slice, 0 for x, 1 for y, and 2 for z.\n\norigin\n\n: Origin of the 2D slice.\n\n# Returns\n\nPlotArgs\n\n# See Also\n\n{func}`pcolormesh`\n"]}, {"name": "pyvlasiator.plot.plot.prep2d", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "meta", "type": {"name": "Vlsv", "xref": {"fqname": "pyvlasiator.vlsv.Vlsv", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "var", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "comp", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Obta